  "prompt": "Is there a survey app which pays at least 5 dollars for easy questions?",
  "response": "There are several survey apps and websites that offer payment for answering questions, but the amount they pay per survey can vary. Some of the more popular options include:\n\n1. **Survey Junkie**: This is a well-known survey site where users can earn money by completing surveys. Surveys typically pay between $1 to $3, but occasionally there may be higher-paying surveys.\n\n2. **Swagbucks**: This platform offers users the opportunity to earn money through a variety of tasks, including surveys. Payment per survey can range from a few cents to several dollars.\n\n3. **Vindale Research**: Vindale Research tends to offer higher-paying surveys, some of which can exceed $5. They might require more time or detailed answers.\n\n4. **InboxDollars**: Similar to Swagbucks, InboxDollars offers payment for various tasks including surveys. Some surveys can pay $5 or more.\n\n5. **Pinecone Research**: Known for higher-paying surveys, usually a flat rate per survey\u2014often around $3 to $5.\n\nWhile these platforms can offer surveys that pay $5 or more, it's important to manage expectations as not every survey will pay this rate\u2014payment depends on the length and complexity of the survey.\n\nAdditionally, not all surveys are 'easy', and higher payment often correlates with surveys that require more time or detailed responses. Make sure to read reviews and understand the payout process for each platform before committing to ensure it's worth your time.",
